message:
Hello people of Cru! I am a Nav girl who has infiltrated your page in search of two female roommates for the 2018-2019 school year. I live with a lovely lady by the name of Kristin Stomberg in Dinnaken Apartments. We are juniors who are seeking women who want to be part of a community where we can grow together in Christ!
Here are the details: two bed, one bath, four people, free laundry, $462/month, utilities are between $25-30 per month in total. Parking is available ($60/month). 
Fun facts: We have cranes on our ceiling and love to bake breads and desserts! 
If you are interested, message me or Kristin Stomberg asap on FB. 
Thanks for reading! Good luck with Finals!

Words of the wise Amy Underwood:

Just a couple days until the women's lock-in which also means there's only a couple more day of class!!!! WOOHOO!! Are you thinking, "Gee, I'm going to have so much studying to do, I don't think I can go"? Well, let me just remind you that Thursday is study day and you deserve a night of fun to celebrate the end of classes. Still not convinced? Here's a list of the awesome things that await you at the lock-in:
-Snacks 
-Competition
-Friendship
-Destressing
-Movies
-Holiday Spirit
-Mug & Muffin
-LOTS OF LOVE AND FUN
So, go ahead and RSVP to the event and put it on the G-cal!!! SEE YOU THERE!!! (If you can only come for part of it, still come!)

message:
The Lord gave me this message:

"I knew you before I formed you in your mother's womb. Before you were born I set you apart and appointed you as my prophet to the nations."

"O Sovereign Lord," I said, "I can't speak for you! I'm too young!"

The Lord replied, "Don't say 'I'm too young,' for you must go wherever I send you and say whatever I tell you. I, the Lord, have spoken!" Then the Lord reached out and touched my mouth and said,

"Look, I have put my words in your mouth! Today I appoint you to stand up against nations and kingdoms. Some you must destroy and tear down, destroy and overthrow. Others you must build up and plant." (Jeremiah 1:4-10)

Ok, so this may not be in the same context as Christ's commission, but it is clear that God can call us to work for him no matter how prepared we think we are to serve him. You do not have to have a doctorate in theology to share your faith. Trust me, I myself still have much to learn. 

Believe it or not, we also have God's presence in the form of the Holy Spirit within us, which is something that even Jeremiah did not have when he prophesied in God's name.

If you are curious about what this looks like in action, I implore you to join us sharing our faith with others at Coffman. We will meet at the top of the escalators in the lobby at 3:30. Soli Deo Gloria.

message:
Hello good people of Cru! Tomorrow morning I will be at Purple Onion from 9-11am having a quiet time and I want you all to join me! As the semester winds down and there's still a million things to do I know it's easy to push off spending time with the Lord. So the point of this is to have a time set where you know you'll be held accountable to actually spending time with Him instead of falling back asleep or being on your phone(both are things that happen to me too often). So come to PO anytime between 9-11am, even if you just have 15 minutes. Lets glorify God by putting him first and giving him some of our morning during this busy season. 
Also if you want to come and spend time with the Lord but you're kinda new to it and don't know what to do with your time I will be bringing some devotional books and would be happy to help you out with that. 
Lastly I would be glad to pray with anyone as well!!
See you tomorrow morning!!!!!

Hey Cru! My house (Evans Scholars) is having a blood drive this Saturday from 11-4. Giving blood is an awesome way to help out people in need. Here are some facts about blood:

Every two seconds in the U.S. someone needs blood

About 7,000 units of platelets and 10,000 units of plasma are needed daily in the U.S.

A single car accident victim may need as many as 100 pints of blood, with the average transfusion being about 3 pints.

There is a huge need for blood every year, and it is the season of giving, so if you are interested in donating, please DM me or comment below so I can give you more details! Take care!

message:
Dear Fellow Crutons, 
I have some sad news to share with you all. After a whole semester's hype of #Lighthouseburning it has come to a reality. 10 random guys signed the lease to our house for the next school year. As Romans 12:15 states, "Rejoice with those who rejoice; mourn with those who mourn." Some will be glad our piece of trash house is burning (Curtis Zicker,) other like myself are mourning over the fact I'll be homeless for a week (hmu if I can stay at your house from August 25th-September 1st). Possible end of year funeral ceremony to come *cough* servant team *cough*

message: MEN OF CRU! I have a friend who is looking for a place to live this coming Spring semester, preferably in a house. He's going to be going to community college, moving from Iowa, so he wants an opportunity to meet new people and get plugged in to a ministry. In addition, he is potentially looking for a place to live next year and loves the idea of being in a house. Is there anything open at least for next semester? Shoot me a message if you think you can help him out! Thanks :)

message:
Hi everyone! For those of you who don't me, I'm Leah (duh). I graduated from the UMN last spring, and started working full time in camp ministry.
I wanted to give UMN Cru friends first notice about an opportunity we have coming up at Camp Victory (it's about an hour from the cities). We have a weekend of camp in winter called Winter Blast! This year, it is February 2-4. If you love camp and retreats as much as I do, you and your friends are MORE than welcome to apply and be a counselor for this year's Winterblast! I wanted to post because I love camp and outdoors, and was always looking for ways to get involved during the school year!

If you are interested, you can message me on Facebook! I hope to see you there!!!

message:
Hey friends! 

Are you looking for opportunities to be more involved with Cru, or do you love talking to people? If you answered yes to one or both of those questions, then I have a great opportunity to share with you!

Before Shift, there is a team of greeters who act as friendly faces to those who are new to Shift/Cru, and also make people smile before they walk through the doors into the Shift service!

We would love to have you join us and volunteer with being a greeter! Sign up with your friends, Bible study, or come meet a new team of volunteers! We need 4 people for each Shift service. Just sign up, and be at the church at 7:30pm on whichever Thursday you signed up for!

Thank you all, and see you at Shift! (:

message:
Hey everyone! David spoke on a very important topic at Shift tonight. Like he said, Matthew 28:18-20 shows that we are commissioned by Christ to go out and be witnesses for him. It is a responsibility of ours as Christians to share our faith with those who are not followers of the Lord. We are fortunate here at the University of Minnesota to be able to freely share our faith with others and, if you unaware, we have organized times during the week where groups of us meet in Coffman to witness to people there. 
That being said, this business of sharing one's faith is easier said than done. I know many of you have reservations about discussing your faith with people on campus, your friends, and even your family members. "I don't know how to share my faith with others." "I don't feel comfortable going out and talking to people about this." If these are some of the thoughts running through your head, then let me remind you that we are not alone in this task. Our groups in Coffman go out in pairs, so you'll have another along side you when you share your faith. More importantly, it is the Holy Sprit that speaks through you when you share the Gospel with others, so your worries and hesitations will be taken away from you. How can you be afraid or hesitant when you have the Lion of Judah at your back?
If you are new to sharing, you can simply watch us speak to others. We will teach and equip you on how to discuss faith with others.

If you are feeling called to act on this commission, I'll be leading a sharing time tomorrow in Coffman at 3:00 pm. Meet at the top of the escalators! Soli Deo Gloria

message:
Hey everyone! A couple friends and I decided last year that we felt there was a void in Christian publishing. There was lots of fluffy stories out there of big name Christians doing big name stuff, but not enough stories of everyday individuals living bold and intentional lives for Christ.

That's why we decided to create a new magazine, THE RISE Magazine. It's a small team of storytellers and story lovers sharing everyday people's stories of faith, pursuit, and excellence.

I thought people in this group might be interest in the project we are working on, so I wanted to share the Kickstarter we launched. 

I'd love for you guys to check it out if you're interested and learn more from our video on the Kickstarter page. Thanks!

message:
Calling all women!!

Are you starting to think about housing next year? Do you want to live in an awesome community of women? Look no further!

I am currently living in the gospel house called the Lighthouse. Living in a gospel has helped me grow in my faith and learn to support one another so much over the 2 years I have lived here. Unfortunately, a lot of us in the house are older and will not be living here next year. We are looking for people to continue the community in this house!

If you are interested in living in a gospel house, or specifically the Lighthouse, please LIKE this. I am planning on having an informational meeting sometime late next week. I will be contacting people early next week about more details about the meeting. 

Hope to see you there!

message:
Hello fellow CRUtons and alumni!
In light of a recent blog post entitled '10 Questions with a Gay Christian' and the ensuing conversations, the Spirit has prompted me to write this post.

First, for those who don't know me, my name is Jared and I attended the U of M from 2010 to 2014. While I came to college looking for what the world had to offer, Christ found me within a matter of weeks in a CRU Bible Study. My fondest memories come from my four years in CRU. Secondly, I used to identify as a homosexual and was an active participant in that lifestyle. Since the onset of puberty I manifested sexual desires exclusively for men. I struggled with lust and pornography just as much (probably much more) than the average male. I even dated another man for a time. My purpose in telling you this is so that you recognize that all 
that I say here comes from an intimate understanding of homosexuality and its bondage. I say all that I do with agonizing compassion for those that wrestle with this particular deviancy and also for anyone who may sympathize with it even if they do not wrestle with it personally.

I realize that the author of said blog post asked for all comments and questions to be directed to her privately, but when something of this magnitude is posted for such a wide audience to see, it requires a public response. Intentionally or not, when you post something on Facebook you are promoting something or teaching something. The purpose of the blog was rather vague; I do not believe it ever explicitly advocated for the affirming of homosexual relationships but the lack of clear warning against them was enough to prompt this post.
 
In this case, what was subtly being taught is that 'gay' and 'Christian' can exist together. Friends, in the interest of being 
brief, this is a false teaching. This is a really, really serious deal. This isn't a choice to be made; there is no "affirming" or "non-affirming," there is no "liberal" Christianity and "conservative" Christianity - there is Christianity and not-Christianity, which includes all things that look very much like Christianity but are not. Paul very explicitly in many places states that the sexually immoral will not inherit the kingdom of God. And not only those who practice it, but those who approve it as well. The very Word of Yahweh has declared those who actively practice homosexuality are sexually immoral, not only in specific verses and passages (see 1 Cor 6:9, 1 Tim 1:10, Lev 18:22, 20:13, Gen 19, Rom 1) but in the macro-view of God's design for human life (see all relationships portrayed in the Bible and how humans procreate). What would Paul say about a Thieving Christian? What about a Murdering Christian? A sin identity is incompatible with the new birth. But again, I do know what it is like to be trapped in an identity. I myself once bought into the lies that I could not change. But by God's grace I really, truly did change. To be clear, the only conversion therapy I condone is just that-conversion. Salvation from sin by the grace given us in Christ Jesus the Son of God. 

So very joyfully, the Word of God does not leave anyone without hope. For God did not send his Son into the world to condemn the world, but in order that the world might be saved through Him. I testify to you that Christ Jesus has come to set people free - not free from problems, not free from low self-esteem, but free from sin! In February of 2015, the Holy Spirit revealed Christ Jesus to me through His Word in Ephesians in such a way that my sins were mortified at the root-I truly am no longer a slave to the lust or envy that I loved. Augustine said it this way: "To Your grace I attribute it, and to Your mercy, that You have melted away my sin as it were ice." And Charles Wesley put it so famously in his hymn: "Thine eye diffused a quickening ray‚ÄîI woke, the dungeon flamed with light;My chains fell off, my heart was free, I rose, went forth, and followed Thee."

Friends, do you know this grace? Has Christ appeared so gloriously to you that you now hate the sin you once loved? I urge you, please ask God whether you do or not. Search His Word and ask for His Spirit to show you Jesus Christ!

This is not a personal attack on anyone. I do not write this to the author or to the participants in the blog, but to the 
spiritual community of CRU as a whole. Questions, comments, angry rants-all welcome. I know very well that this post was not perfect but I am not ashamed of the Gospel because it is the power of God for salvation to everyone who believes!

We're gonna meet at Saint Lawrence Catholic Church, play dodgeball (hopefully at least a couple games vividly reenacting the protestant reformation), then go hang at the SPO men's house on 7th Street next to the tree house.  I think I invited most of the guys in this group, but if I missed you or you want to let your bible study guys know, just comment here and we'll send you/them an invite.  It'll be laid back, and the SPO guys are awesome if you haven't met them.  Hopefully see all of you guys there!

message:
Hi people, 
Wish I knew all you fine folks, I recently joined the Cru staff and mission here at the U. 
We have an open door to do world missions right here on campus! 
Students are here from many nations! 

One way is to offer to be a conversation partner with a class mate who speaks English as a 2nd language!

The commitment to be a conversation partner includes:
Meeting up twice a month with your partner
Having the desire and margin to spend time with your partner outside of your 2 meetings
Attending a conversation partner training once a semester

If you have any questions about the role or commitment please ask me or Jen Berglund Eggers. 

Here is the sign up form. Please respond by Sunday: https://goo.gl/forms/w5WlKePD0VgjzC7N2

Another opportunity!

Hindu Training/ outreach to students from India

Bonus announcement: ISM (the ministries that put on English Club including Cru) have a guest speaker coming to teach about ministering to Hindu /Indian students.
It will be September 24th at 
5:30 -7pm at Stadium Village Church. 
You and your friends are welcome!

Questions..Frank 612-221-0924

message: Bridges is hosting English Club this week! Woohoo! English Club is essentially a club for international students and american students to hang out, eat a free meal, and practice their English conversational skills.  We would love to see some of you guys there! (Also, there's going to be free homemade Indian food!!!)

message:
Hello friends!!
If you don't know, anyone can get into any of the frats this weekend, so it's one of the weekends where campus is a little more dangerous to be walking at night. It's also one of the weekends where sexual assault is most prevalent on our campus.

Because of this, there is a group of us that will be out Friday night (11-2ish maybe?) with bottled water and everystudent.com bracelets to walk people (okay- women) back to their dorms/apartments safely.

Looking for people who are wanting to be a light to our campus with us! Let's plan on meeting at 11pm on Friday (after the movie night if you're leading freshmen) outside the Treehouse to buddy up and go from there. 

(Also, if you haven't checked out the every student website, link is below üòä).

(Also, if you're coming and could pitch in for waters that would be spectacular).

HI FRIENDS. I have a message to deliver from our good friend Hailey from Hawaii (she used to be in Cru but alas she is now back in Hawaii, no longer a student at the U, and can't access this page): 

"Wanna spend next summer in Hawaii? Come join Pacific House of Mission & work with military youth (6th-12th grade) on multiple military bases on Oahu, HI. You'll spend your summer planning & leading weekly bible studies, coordinating sports nights and special events for the youth throughout the summer, and building relationships with the staff & youth. Feel free to send me an email @ hailey.shaul14@gmail.com even if you're slightly interested!! I'd be happy to answer any questions you might have :) 

http://www.pacifichouseofmission.com/internship-program/ "

message:
Hey Cru :) Looking for a FUN job near the U of M that will work around your class schedule? ACR Homes is HIRING direct care professionals! See for yourself how incredible this company is, and how their VALUES impact the quality of care for the residents and the satisfaction of employees. I worked for ACR Homes during my Kinesiology undergrad, Occupational Therapy grad program, and I continue to work for them even after obtaining an OT position because I love this company! 
Email me to get more info, ask questions, or apply! osbo0206@umn.edu

message:
Hello! 
Some of you may know that Jacklyn George used to host a wellness brunch for those struggling with mental health. I would love to continue that tradition this summer and next fall, but I need a group of people to join me! If anyone is looking for a group to discuss mental health issues in a Christian, loving community of people, this is the group for you! Please contact me if you are at all interested and we will start coming up with meeting times!

No one should struggle alone. I love you and want to share your burden and help you heal. 

Peace and blessings ‚ù§Ô∏è
Chloe

message:
MEN!!!
If you are looking for a short-term ministry working with kids this summer I have the perfect ONE WEEK AND FREE opportunity for you! My home church is looking for boys camp counselors from July 23- July 28 at our camp, Camp Patmos, up north in Hackensack, MN for our elementary-aged (2nd-5th grade) week. It's an overnight camp where we get to share the gospel and plant seeds to help kids grow in their faith. Camp Patmos is where I actually started to understand what a personal relationship with Jesus looks like and where I committed my life to Him! It's pretty much my favorite place on earth so if you are at all interested please personal message me or text me (612-419-2420) and I'll get you connected(: 

Have a great Memorial Day!

message:
Dearest Crutons,

I hope finals ended/are ending well! I have an important request:

Student Unions & Activities is working on involvement campaigns for next year and would like a few (like 3ish) students from Cru for a photo. You would all have to go to Coffman anytime from 9:00-5:30 next Tues (5/16) or Thurs (5/18).

Please message me if this is something in which you would be interested! Thanks so much, and as Lauren Otto says, "has a summer!"

Good morning Cru! Fired up by the Twins win last night? Want to watch more (hopefully) winning baseball/softball? You're in luck!

Come watch the Cru softball team in the playoffs TONIGHT!!! The semifinal is at 6:30, and if/when we win that, the final is at 9:00! I know Coach Homan would love a passionate fan section, and rumor has it that Lauren Otto will be making an appearance, so there's no reason not to go!

Games are at the softball fields where the dome used to be. Ask Haley Trewin for directions.

THANKS and see you there! #BuildTheHype #SeeYouAtTheSoftballFields

message:
Hi friends!!

My friend Theresa, who works for Midwest Dairy, is helping coordinate Midwest Dairy's annual princess event and is looking for one or two people (no gender preference) to lead a nondenominational worship service for ~20-30 people on Saturday, May 20 at St. Ben's in St. Cloud. The service would be 30-60 minutes and begin around 5 p.m. Typically, they have only had Catholic mass, but they want to provide an option to the girls who are not Catholic.

The person or persons would give a few readings, lead prayer and share a message. Theresa also said they could provide some video sound from YouTube if you have sound ideas.

I am not able to do it, but I would love to see someone provide this opportunity for the girls and preach the gospel message.

Message me if you're interested ASAP!! Thanks all!

message:
Hey ya'll
The National Day of Prayer is happening THIS WEEK - May 4th

It is a little different this year being outside of the US Bank Stadium, but the focus is less about the musicians, speakers and the venue

It's about Jesus being the main event and for us to come together as one large body of believers to ask God for healing, revival, the small things and the big 

If anyone wants to go with me I will be riding the train over there for the night! Take a break from studying to worship the God who has blessed us with education here at the U of M
He is worthy of our praise.

message: Hey everybody, with the last Shift being yesterday, I just wanted to say: thanks for a great year of community and mems! message:
Hey peeps! A couple of things: 
First, I'm wondering if anyone is going to Hope tonight for Gospel and Race and would be able to give me a ride back to DInkytown? 
Second, sharing today at Coffman 1-2pm! There's only this week and next week left, so if you haven't made it to sharing yet this year or only have gone once or twice, the Go Be The Voice team would like to encourage you to step out of your comfort zone and come serve alongside us before the semester wraps up. I'd love to see ya today!!!

Hey All! Me and a few friends (Alec McElhinny and Axl Harlander) are trying to find a sub-leasers for our apartment this summer. It's a 2 bedroom double occupancy apartment in DinkyTown at the Marshall and you'll be living with the amazing Erik Johnson as well. We are setting the rent at $400 per month. So please feel free to contact us if interested or if you want to negotiate the price.

message: Summer bible study is coming back this summer!! For those who don't know what it is, it is a time to continue to develop and grow your walk with Christ as well as your community during the summer! David Morelli Emily Wydo and I will be leading it, and just wanted to gauge interest/when people are free! If you could fill out the google form below, we would greatly appreciate it (it'll take less than a minute)! Feel free to contact any of us if you have questions! Get hyped!!!

HEY SENIORS! Julia and I are planning for your senior send-off next week at Shift and need some information from you! Please send a slide to trewi001@umn.edu and asmus070@umn.edu with your name (and a photo of yourself if you want), your plans for after graduation, and some piece of advice to share with all of us underclassmen.

We need this slide from you by Monday (this would be underlined and bolded if Facebook would let me) at the very latest or your slide will not be included. 

Have a rad week. :)

message:
Hey guys! This past winter break I went to Israel with Passages. They are an organization that is passionate about sending Christian college students to Israel. The trip is almost entirely covered by the organization. Here is the address if you want to check out their website: http://passagesisrael.org/ 

My time in Israel was absolutely incredible and I wanted other students from the U of M to have the same opportunity. I am working with the directors of the organization to send a bus from MN from December 31st - Jan 11th. If anyone is interested in hearing about my time in Israel, I am sharing about it next Thursday (4/13) at 7:30 PM at Coffman in room 305. 

If you are thinking, who is this person? I don't want to hear them talk. Then you can just come to the informational meeting with two of the directors of the organization at 8:30 PM. If you come to the interest meeting, there is no obligation to go, it is just a place to ask questions!

My email is haszx008@umn.edu. Feel free to email me if you are interested in the trip or have questions or want to know how much I ended up paying (like I said its almost entirely covered)! 

I hope to see some of you next week! Sorry for the long post!

See you at the top of the escalators at 3!!!

message:
Okay I know what you're thinking, "wow Ella had such an incredible amount of talent in 2010, when is she going to make a come-back video to share with the world??"

Well folks, I can't guarantee a new video to share with you (sry for the disappointment, but I'm not saying it's impossible), but I can guarantee SHARING the Gospel with students on campus today with Nicholas Schleif and Micah J. Farenik!!!! 

Jokes aside we'd love to have you join us from 1-2pm in Coffman to connect with and care for the many students here at the U, better understanding their backgrounds and spreading the word of the Gospel with them! Per usual, meet at the escalators!

message:
HEY FRIENDS!!!!!!

It has been so exciting to see many of you take steps of faith this year by sharing for the first time!!! It has also been extremely encouraging to see your passion for it as you guys continue to make it a priority week after week!!!!! :') 

BUT THE BEST PART IS, WE STILL HAVE LIKE 5 OR 6 WEEKS LEFT OF SCHOOL OR SOMETHING (Idk I'm bad at counting)! SO LETS KEEP GOING STRONG!!! 

Come join Nicholas Schleif, Lauren Otto, Chaz Fenske, and other cool humans sharing today in Coffman from 2:30-3:30!!!! We would love to see you there!!!!!

SEE YOU AT THE TOP OF THE ESCALATORS!!!!!

message:
Evening,

Tomorrow myself and Michael Francis will be meeting for project abide at the Purple Onion from 8-10/11
I would love love LOVE to see some of y'all come out to study God's word and witness to the people around you. (Check 1 Timothy 4:11-13, good stuff there)

Cool thing though:
If you were @ Shift last night you heard about the organic prayer gatherings that were happening
If you want your Friday soaked in Jesus, come earlier and join me in prayer @ 7:30 am for our campus and whatever/whoever else may be on your mind and stick around for a quiet time! 

Reach out to me with any questions
Peace n' blessings.
Emily - out.

Hello everyone!! 
As some of you know I will be going to Alaska for Cru Summer Missions, and there will be a group of 10+ people driving to Juneau. message:
Men!  Dudes and Doughnuts!  It's happening this Saturday at 10 am, and if you have no idea what this is, comment here and we'll get you added to the event, but just to sate your appetite for more information until you see the event, here's a taste: We're getting together this Saturday morning, just the dudes, and spending some quality time together as Men.  We'll be getting off campus, getting outside, eating doughnuts, and spending time with the Lord TOGETHER.  It's gonna be AWESOME.

If you're a guy and can drive, also reach out to me and let me know, because we'll need some drivers to get us where we're going (it won't be a long drive, staying in the cities).

I will see YOU men on Saturday

GUYS DONT BE LIKE AUTUMN, REGISTER FOR BIG BREAK! TODAY IS THE LAST DAY!!

The link to register is http://www.big-break.com and make sure to choose Panama City Beach 2 when registering! 

****If finances are a problem PLEASE contact Michael Francis (franc515@umn.edu) with any questions about scholarship opportunities, we don't want finances to be the reason someone doesn't come with us

Have a wonderful Friday, see you at the beach in 2 weeks!!!!! #buildthehype #seeyouatthebeach #itslitty

message:
Hello, Gophers! 
Are you still unsure of what you want to do this summer? Cause same! Do you want 10 weeks of free food, a free place to stay, and to get paid for it?! Consider working at Luther Point Bible Camp, in the lovely Grantsburg, Wis.  for a summer! If you love outdoor ministry, working with kids, and living on a lake, this is the place for you! 
If this is something that interests you, feel free to message me, or check it out for yourself on lutherpoint.org. 

I hope you have enjoyed this shameless plug!

Stay Classy CruGophs!

message:
Hello wonderful people of Cru!
So I have good news and bad news for y'all and I'm going to start with the bad news.
The bad news is that Emily Wydo has recently had some accusations made against her by the public (see below) and cannot lead sharing today.
The good news is that Manmaker and Women's Retreat start in just a few hours! Because registration starts at 5, Curtis Zicker and I have made an executive decision to not hold a Friday sharing time this week. But, we will be holding one next week and would love to have you join us! Have an amazing weekend at Manmaker and Women's Retreat everyone!

If you care to know more about the accusations made against Emily, please watch this very informative YouTube video.

LOOKING FOR SUMMER SUBLET @ The Marshall
 
I'm looking for female sublet for the summer at The Marshall in Dinkytown, mid-May through August (I'll pay rent for the month of May). The apartment is a 2 bed/2 bath. You would be sharing a room and a bathroom with one other person. Rent also includes an underground garage parking spot. Utilities are around 15-20 dollars a month.

Rent is $535 and the parking spot is $135. I am willing to negotiate. Message me if you're interested or if you know anyone that would be interested!!

message: Hello friends! So Emily Wydo was planning to lead a sharing time today. However, since the devastating annihilation of the Packers on Sunday, she has gone into exile on the desert planet of Tatooine in a desperate attempt to preserve Packer fandom for future generations. Lucky for you, Katherine and I will be leading the time today from 4-5 pm in Coffman! Some great conversations were started last night at the foundations forum, and we'd love to continue those on campus today and share God's love with our fellow students. So whether you've been a bazillion times before or zero times, please come join us! See you at the top of the escalators at 4!

message:
Good morning everyone! I will be leading a sharing time every Thursday 1-2pm and I am looking forward to meeting students on campus to share with them the Good News of the Gospel alongside you--newcomers and returners!

However, today I will not be sharing because of a commitment I had before setting up times. BUT I would still encourage you to grab a group of friends and share around Coffman if God has placed it on your heart to join me each week! If you don't want to go out sharing yet, that's okay too--what about just sitting at Coffman during that hour long time and praying over our campus, the students, and the sovereign plans that the Lord has for each one of us? God is moving and He has started a good work in us that He will see is finished!

Enjoy the rest of your week and I'll see you next Thursday!

message:
Hey all! Have you ever wanted to get into scripture alone but have no idea where to start? Have you ever wanted to get into the word regularly but have not been able to set and stick with a time? I definitely have.  If so, join me tomorrow morning at the Purple Onion for this semesters launch of Project Abide.

Where: Purple Onion Cafe 

When: 8-10AM (Come for however long!) 

Why: Super encouraging to pray and be at peace with the semester and learn from God's Word.

What: Come in, read and pray. Discuss things from the Bible that may be tough to understand with the goal of learning together! 

Hope to see you tomorrow!

As a prize for reading to the end, I will buy the drink of the first 2 people who show up to study the Word!

If you are going to Cru Winter Conference, please sign this petition.

It is incredibly important to the time honored tradition of Cru's Winter Conference that UMN Cru goes to Salsa a la Salsa at some point throughout the conference.

"Salsa a la Salsa is the most authentic Mexican restaurant in the state of Minnesota. It's pretty good." - Jon Oliversen

Guys: gold shirt of some sort
Girls: maroon shirt of some sort 

Bring extras if you have them!!!!

Gooooood Evening Gopher Cru!

If you were at Shift last night you heard me say I'd be posting the links to where to sign up for Cru Winter Conference (CWC, C Dub C etc. etc.) and where to sign up for a scholarship!

If money is a problem, we will get you there - do not NOT sign up if money is the ONLY reason you are holding back from going.
And if you want to be considered to pie myself (pls not me, all other advertisements that I wanted to be, are false) or one of the other fireseeds in the face sign up BY TONIGHT.

*disclaimer - if you want to apply for a scholarship, you need to sign up for the conference first!

Peace n' Blessings.

Sign up here! https://www.cru.org/communities/campus/winterconference.html

Hey guys! In two days the Christian Student Union (https://www.facebook.com/CSUUMN/?fref=ts) will be hosting our December One Church. This is a worship and prayer night, and there will also be coffee and specialty drinks (by Humble Cup), Christmas cookies, mittens for sale (by Higher Trail mittens, a local one-for-one mitten company) (https://www.facebook.com/highertrail/?fref=ts), and some great fellowship before and after the service. 

Come take a break from studying and enjoy fellowship while celebrating the Christmas season! 

We hope to see you there!

Reminder: Only 10 (very soon to be 9) days left to sign up for CWC before price goes up. In case you're still unsure, here are some pros and cons of going to CWC to help you make a decision: 

Pros:
1) If 150 U of M students sign up, rumor has it that Connor Lund will be re-enacting his heart-rending 2012 cover of Call Me Maybe, live at the Hilton. (link for the uninitiated: https://www.facebook.com/connor.lund.731/videos/t.100000091875627/493170210696037/?type=2&theater)

2) You'll get to witness Charles Schaller's performance of the Bema Seat, which is a life-changing experience. 

3) Early reports seem to indicate that Nick Anderson will be in attendance.

Cons:
.

Here's the link to sign up!
https://www.cru.org/communities/campus/winterconference.html

message:
Hey guys!
If any of you are looking for something to do tonight, my friends and I have put together a charity fundraiser concert at the Art House North in Saint Paul! There's a variety show at 4:30 and then Early Eyes and The Happy Children will be performing later on. Tickets will be $6 at the door, and all the money raised is going straight to the Malala fund to support education for girls around the world. Hope to see some of you there! :)

message:
Hello Ladies! So my friend Alyssa Burk and I are looking for two more girls to live with us in a two bedroom, two bath apartment at the Venue next year. Rent would be around $600 a month and the building has two work out areas, two lounge rooms, and a study room, with free printing and computers. This gives plenty of space to get work done, stay healthy, and be close to campus. We are both freshman, pretty chill, and like to have fun, but we also stay on top of school work. We also love cats, Gilmore Girls, and Jesus, so if you wanted to get to know us more or be our roommate, feel free to message one of us!
My cell: 651-491-2107

HEY!!!!! Do you want to know what Kallie Erickson (aka your shift emcee and a super cool human) does outside of Cru? Well, she's on the exec team for Minnesota Dance Marathon and helps raise money for the Gillette Children's Hospital. 

Now I know you're thinking, "WOW THATS SO COOL. KALLIE IS SO COOL. HOW CAN I SPEND EIGHT CONSECUTIVE HOURS WITH THIS COOL HUMAN?" 

Well lucky for you I have an answer:
 
YOU CAN REGISTER FOR DANCE MARATHON BECAUSE IT WILL BE FUN AND YOU GET TO SUPPORT GILLETTE CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL AND HANG WITH FRIENDS (like Kallie) AND PLAY GAMES AND SEE CUTE KIDS (like Jackson in the picture below) AND DANCE AND I CANT THINK OF A BETTER WAY TO SPEND YOUR FEBRUARY 11TH FROM 12-8PM

AND THERES EVEN A CRU TEAM. 
¬Ø\_(„ÉÑ)_/¬Ø 

AND ALSO ALSO, IF YOU REGISTER BY TONIGHT (www.minnesotadm.org) AND USE THE CODE "Hope50" ITS ONLY FIVE DOLLARS. CRAZY. I KNOW.

If you have any questions ask Kallie or Emily Zibrowski

message:
Hi everyone! Knowing that you all are super awesome supporting people, I wanted to post some info about a Habitat for Humanity fundraiser below. You literally just have to eat chicken at Cane's before SHIFT on Wednesday to support it, so grab some friends and go :)! Thanks!

This Wednesday, Habitat for Humanity will be hosting a restaurant fundraiser from 6-8pm at Raising Cane's chicken in Stadium Village. If you have dinner at Raising Cane's during this time and say that you are there for the Habitat for Humanity fundraiser, 15% of your purchase goes directly to Habitat for Humanity. HOW COOL IS THAT!! 

So for those who are usually too busy to do any community support events, this is your chance. All you have to do is eat chicken! Pretty easy. See ya Wednesday at Cane's at 6!

message:
Hey everyone!

This Sunday at 3:00 PM there will be an open house at the Grandpa Green! This will actually be an event for women who are looking for gospel housing (yes, WOMEN!). The men currently living at the Grandpa Green, myself included, will not be living there next year, but we would love to see it continue on as a CRU house! We know that there is more of a demand from women who want to live in gospel housing so we are opening it up to them to take over the Grandpa (Grandma???) Green for next year!

We will have treats for the women who would like to take a look around the house and the basics of what taking over the house would look like. If you are at all interested please send either Luke Hemphill or Myself a message!

Thank You!

message:
HEY MY PPL!!! A really accessible way to support our brothers and sisters with black and brown skin is to LEARN ABOUT THEM!!!!! Whiteness affords the majority of us opportunities that lead to ignorance of privilege. As registration approaches, I encourage you to take an ethnic/gender studies class to educate yourself on how we can LOVE and SUPPORT our friends of color well in a society that favors majority culture. I'm taking Introduction to African American Studies on Mondays and Wednesdays. Join me!!! It would be so so fun to take a class with ya'll. I know you have credits to fill. 

Here's some info on one of MANY options. 

AFRO 1011-001
(52721)
MoWe 1:00PM - 2:15PM
Blegen Hall 240
R. Brewer
3.00 Creds

message:
Hello! If you guys like kids and dancing you should register for Minnesota Dance Marathon! It is a student group who raises money for Gillette Children's Hospital by hosting an 8 hour dance marathon on Feb 11th at the Rec from 12pm-8pm! 

S/O to Zach Bleakly for creating a team for CRU for you all to register on! It takes less than 2 minutes to sign up for 8 hours of awesome fun! Sign up at www.minnesotadm.org

Also, Autumn Beckman is the emcee so come support your CRU friends!

message:
Hey guys, here is a message from your local habitat for humanity chapter. Check it out!

Do you have plans for winter break? The UMN Habitat for Humanity Chapter currently has openings in their alternative winter break trips! The dates of the trip are January 8, 2017 - January 14, 2017.

Here is a general overview of what a winter break trip with Habitat for Humanity entails:

work Monday through Friday from approximately 8 a.m. to 4 p.m.
projects may include improving existing housing structures, helping build a house or volunteering on other projects that help meet the goals of Habitat for Humanity in the community
evenings to be free to use as your group desires (visit the beach, explore the town, etc.)
Locations include:

York, Pennsylvania 
Winston-Salem, North Carolina
New Smyrna, Florida
Email toni.marano@uofmhabitat.org  for more information!He

message:
Mornin'
So Tuesday sharing is picking up where we left off. I'll be going as always from 5:30-6:30 in Coffman! Meet me at the top of the escalators.
If you've never been, I personally invite you to come with the team that has assembled over the past few weeks. We are more than happy to help you and let you watch if you're uncomfortable! I promise, the more you do it, the easier it gets (practice makes perfect, right?)

Sharing is simply the act of praising God for what He has done by letting as many people as we can know about the Good News that was once shared with us. 
Because like TBH I don't know what I would do without Jesus rn in the midst of midterms and just general college life. 

(PS don't forget to get out and vote!)
Peace n' blessings.

message:
SVC Work day tomorrow, 9am-12pm. Let's help them clean and fix up the church, and do some outside yard work. 

Stadium Village Church is having a work day from 9am-12pm tomorrow, Saturday, Nov 5th, followed by a chili lunch (The Gopher game is at 2:30, so you won't miss it). 

Pastor Lowell has asked if some Cru students could help. I know there's been quite a bit going on this week with Justice Week, but I think it would be awesome to have a bunch of us serve the church by helping with the work day. They are a great ministry to the U of M campus, and a great blessing to Cru for letting us use their facility for Shift. Let's give back and bless them with TONS of help this Saturday. 

Please consider serving for all or part of the time. 
Comment on here, or email me if you can help. (Ryan.carlson@cru.org)

message: Hello! Tonight is the last big event of Justice Week! We will be watching Nefarious tonight at 8pm in Nicholson Hall room 275. This documentary is worth your time. If it were to be a movie just for fun or hanging out with people and you have homework to do or an exam to study for, I'd tell you to skip it. But this movie is worth your time and I'd love to see you all tonight to learn honest stories of injustice, but also stories of hope. Bring a snack and a friend!

message:
There is a great opportunity to serve this weekend! 

Stadium Village Church is having a work day from 9am-12pm this Saturday, Nov 5th, followed by a chili lunch (The Gopher game is at 2:30, so you won't miss it). 

Pastor Lowell has asked if some Cru students could help. I know there's a lot going on this week with Justice Week, but I think it would be awesome to have a bunch of us serve the church by helping with the work day. They are a great ministry to the U of M campus, and a great blessing to Cru for letting us use their facility for Shift. Let's give back and bless them with TONS of help this Saturday. 

Please consider serving for all or part of the time. 
Comment on here, or email me if you can help. (Ryan.carlson@cru.org)

message: Hey Cru! Yesterday at the Mosaic we had a ton of girls come to check out gospel housing and we noticed that there is a lot more demand this year than there are spots for our current Gospel Houses, which is super exciting!!!! In the past there has been a spreadsheet for people to sign up on so you can see other Christians who are interested in living in Gospel housing as well. We would love to see new gospel communities get started! Be praying about how you could be a part of starting a new cru community with some awesome people! Here is a spreadsheet to fill out your information and I'm sure if you asked any of your leaders, friends or myself, they would be willing to help you out in any way to start a new gospel living community!!!!

message: Bored because you have nothing to do over winter break besides TCX? Well look no further because you should apply for LeaderShape. Unless you're not in CSE/Carlson/CFans, then look further since you aren't eligible. It's an awesome 6 day retreat at Camp Ihduhapi like 40 minutes from campus to learn leadership skills, vision planning, integrity, etc. It also counts for an honor experience if you're into that stuff. Deadline is November 11 to apply

message:
Hey friends!

The first One Church of the year is this Saturday at Stadium Village Church!  Starting at 6:30 we will have free drip coffee and $2 lattes from Humble Cup (bring cash).  Worship will start at 7!

We would love to have you join us as we seek to bring unity to the body of Christ on campus.  

If you aren't sure what One Church is, it is a community wide worship night with the goal of bringing together all the campus ministries in a night of worshipping Jesus and prayer!

Hope to see you there!

GOOOOOD MORNING UMN CRU -
I am here to give a S/O for the Tuesday sharing time from 5:30-6:30 in Coffman
These past two weeks we have had so many new faces. It's been encouraging to watch you all take steps of faith to share Christ with your fellow Gophers. 
As always, if you have never been, I personally invite you to come share with me, I am not perfect at it myself, but with practice and shadowing experienced people you learn to articulate your faith in ways you never have been able to before. 

See you @ the top of the escalators! 
Peace n' blessings

message: Hey guys!  I have a job opportunity for anyone interested in making a little extra cash!  Every Monday from 8-2 a family who lives in South Minneapolis would love a babysitter.  They live about 10 minutes from campus if there is traffic so it's pretty convenient!    They have three little boys who love walks, playing at the park, and riding the scooter.  The last hour and a half they all take naps so it's pretty easy.  Please message me personally if you are interested and/or have questions!

Good morning everyone! We will not be having prayer group today. But don't worry, join us during Justice Week next week during one of the three prayer walks! 

We will be meeting in the mall area in front of Walter all three times. Hope to see you at at least one of the three times!

Monday: 3:30-4:30
Tuesday: 12:30-1:30
Friday: 3:30-4:30

message:
Hello friends! If anyone in here likes the band Remedy Drive, they're putting on a concert at my home church! It's in a little less than 2 weeks, on Friday, November 4th, at 7 PM. For those of you that don't know them, they're a great Christian rock band! 

Its at Peace Church in Eagan, MN, its about 25 minutes away, and its super easy to get to there driving or theres even a metro bus that takes you to the Eagan Outlet mall, which is about a quarter mile away from the church. 

In the photo is all the details! I hope some of you guys can make it! 

Below is the link to buy tickets! They are $15 at the door, $12 Presale, or $8 Group rate of 10 or more in a group.

https://peaceeagan.breezechms.com/form/3c2834

message: If anyone's looking for a historical perspectives lib-ed or thinks a religious studies minor would be cool (cuz it is) or needs a fun class, you should look into RELS 1082 Jesus in History. It covers the four gospels, other writings like Gospel of Judas, and watches movies like Jesus Christ Superstar and Matrix to figure out how they represent Jesus. Professor for it is really cool and they need more students to register so they can have more TAs and have a reason to pay grad students. If you're doing the minor, you can also email prof to set up independent study with an extra paper or two for 3xxx credit. Link for it is here

message:
Friends I woke up this morning feeling extremely grateful that I am known and loved by the God of the universe, and that I DO know this to be true.
That being said, today you could maybe have the opportunity to share that with someone who may have never heard this good news before.
I am going sharing in Coffman today from 5:30-6:30 
As always I encourage those who have never been before to join me.
The thoughts you may have like "I've never done it before" or "I don't know how" are not valid anymore, because there are people who are excited to show/teach you how sharing works!!!!
So I'll see YOU @ the top of the escalators 
Have a great Tuesday everyone!

message:
Post Fall Retreat blues got ya down? What better way to fix that than some high-quality sharing experience this afternoon 4:30-5:30 in Coffman! 

In all seriousness though, these sharing times that Go Be The Voice has set up throughout the week are incredible opportunities for you to reach out to the students on this campus and share with them the Good News that we can have the gift of eternal life and an intimate relationship with the Creator of our universe. 

Maybe you felt challenged this weekend at Fall Retreat to evangelize, maybe you felt convicted by the fears and lies that prevent you from sharing your faith. I'd love to walk along side you, help you take that leap of faith, and lead you by the guidance and grace of our Father.

I encourage you to take some time to consider going out sharing at least once this semester--you never know what mountains God will move for the sake of His Kingdom. I'll be at Coffman this afternoon and I'd love to see you there!

Have an awesome Monday and don't forget that you are SO loved!

message: Who's pumped for fall retreat?! I know I am! On a different note, if you're a guy in Cru and you're interested in checking out Gospel housing for next year, the Grandpa Green is hoping to get at least 5 new guys for next year! Gospel housing has been an amazing experience and I would highly recommend it. I mean where else can you live in a community of like minded individuals who love Jesus? That being said, if you're interested in living at Grandpa Green next year, we'll be holding tours/info sessions on Sunday evenings. You'll get to eat dinner with all the roomies and we'll tell you everything you need to know. If you're interested, you can message me or text me at 612-986-2098. See you all at fall retreat!

If you have never been before, you can absolutely still come and we will teach you/show you how to start a conversation about faith. (it is scary, I know) 

For the Spirit God gave us does not make us timid, but gives us power, love and self-discipline. So do not be ashamed of the testimony about our Lord or of me his prisoner (Paul). Rather, join with me in suffering for the gospel, by the power of God. -  2 Timothy 1:7-8

Hey yall!
A group of us is going to go tell people about Jesus in Coffman Memorial Union from 4:00 to 5:00 today! It's been a week full of posts about sharing, but let's finish out strong! If you haven't been sharing yet this week, come! If you've been out already, come again! If your scared or tired, what a better way to sacrifice to the Lord. Meet at the top of the escalators. See yall there!

message:
Hello Friends!

If you're looking for something AWESOME to do next weekend, check out Agape Dance Collective's first show! We are striving to minister to the arts community, and we have created a show with a vision to tackle important and tough questions about God and our humanity through movement. Ministry in the arts community is TOUGH, and we'd love to have your support. Plus, there are some absolutely beautiful movers in this show.

Check out our Facebook page (you can find all the event details under the "events" tab): https://www.facebook.com/agapedancecollective/?fref=ts

and here is our kickstarter campaign, we have a video and tons of other info: https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1869710723/agape-dance-collective/description

Thanks guys!

message: Is there a group going swing dancing tonight? There are four Frontier freshmen wanting to go, and they were wondering if anyone could give them a ride.

Hey everyone! I will be going sharing today from 4:00 - 5:00 and I want you to join me! After listening to Angela's talk last night, I keep thinking of 1 John 4:19 which says, "We love because he first loved us." In my mind there is no greater way to show love to our fellow gophers than to share the love that God has shown each of us. Will you join me in bringing a message of hope and peace to our campus today? Meet at the top of the escalators in Coffman! See you there! #GoBeTheVoice

message:
Men, women, I graduated in 2015 and probably half of you don't even know who I am, and that's okay.  

I just wanted to say that I am so unbelievably encouraged and warmed to the heart to see how many people are posting about going sharing and getting Jesus out to the campus;  I literally just teared up with joy while sitting on my sofa just from scrolling through this page.  
Thank you all, do it with all your heart for the worthy Lord.  Lean into Him more and more and find that His goodness it sufficient.

message:
Good Morning ya'll!
It is Tuesday (duh) which means today (and every Tuesday for the rest of the semester) I will be going sharing in Coffman 
For those who do not know what 'sharing' is - it's basically telling people who Jesus is and why it means something for their life.
I am leading from 5:30-6:30 - you can meet me at the top of the escalators then!
I have word that Calvin, Haley, Nick and probably Ashlinn will be joining me!
If you have never been but want to learn or see how sharing works, I will personally partner with you! 
Hope to see you there!
Peace n' Blessings

message:
Hey homies, this semester's sharing times officially begin today! Join me at 4:30pm at the top of the escalators in Coffman for an hour of going out and meeting people on campus and sharing the Gospel! If you've never gone sharing or shared your faith before, use this ministry as an awesome opportunity to connect with others on campus and discover God's calling for us to spread His Word. If you have already gone sharing, please feel encouraged to continue to do so! 
There are many times throughout the week for you to go sharing, and if there isn't already a set time that works for you, consider starting your own (check out the spreadsheet). The Go Be The Voice team is so excited to see what God has in store for our campus this year and we're excited to see our team grow!

message:
Hey everyone! I am the Vice President of Cru this year and one of things I want to do is hear from you.  How are we going to do this??? I'll be at Purple Onion (1301 University Ave SE) from 9:30-10:30 AM on Wednesdays this semester chilling.  Please come in and talk to me if you

1. Have any questions about Cru or what we do on campus
2. Have any topics to discuss about the Bible or Christianity
3. Have ideas for areas of improvement for our group or ways Cru could better care for students at the U of MN

I would really appreciate hearing your thoughts and opinions!  Thank you all! I'll update if the time changes during the semester and fire up for Fall!

Hey ya'll! 
so it's a new school year which means - new people to share the Good News with!
A few of us have been 'put in charge' to start leading times this year
please take a look at the Google document to see the new sharing times
If none of these work for you but you feel compelled 'to go' PLEASE, set up a new time!
Anyone can edit this document
You can also add your name to the times already laid out
We will be starting officially next week on Monday (so everyone can get their schedules established)
If you have any questions contact me, Ella Borgenheimer, Peter Kelly, Autumn Beckman, or David Morelli

Peace n' blessings

message:
Wellness Brunch is still a thing this year! If you or someone you know/meet struggles with anxiety, depression, or any other mental wellness struggle, message me! We get together and eat waffles and talk about what we're going through and our relationship with God and stuff. It's veerrryyyyy helpful to not feel so alone. 

If u come across somebody who deals with mental wellness and feel ill equipped to help them, I'd love to get coffee with them! Or you! Or both! I dealt with anxiety and depression very severely for most of my life and the Lord has given me a good deal of wisdom on the topic :)

Hi All! 

There is big need for PIANO TEACHERS in the Edina/Bloomington area through a company called MusicLink. You would need a car. Piano experience required, but no teaching experience required. I've taught there the past two years and the lady that runs it is really great to work with. She sets up all the lessons and collects payments so all you would have to do is show up. Respond or message me if you're interested. I'd be happy to answer any other questions you might have. Thanks!

message:
Hello Everyone!

Over these past couple days, our country, community, others communities, families, friends, and many others have been hurt, angry, and full of heavy hearts. I know for myself, I have been constantly processing what is happening. Many have been brought to tears by the way many are responding, the hurt many are feeling, and the brokenness our country is experiencing. 

But let‚Äôs all stop and ask ourselves how God wants us to respond. In Acts 12, Peter was captured and put in prison by King Herod, shortly after the king had killed James. How did the Church respond? They gathered together. And what did they do after they gathered together? They prayed and continued to pray until Peter showed up at their door. 

Right now God is calling us. He is teaching us how to solve impossible problems. It‚Äôs very simple: we must pray. God moves in a direct response to prayer, so that is what we must do now.

I‚Äôm inviting you all to come together as a church and pray. Come to the mall tomorrow morning to join together as one and pray for our country, the black community, the police community, the loved ones affected, and any others who are feeling hurt and broken. Invite others to pray as well. 

Hope to see you tomorrow morning at 11am in the mall (at the U of M).

‚Ä¶‚Ä¶

I also encourage you to gather and pray, even if you are unable to come together on campus tomorrow morning. Find others and pray.

message:
Dearest ladies/gents/kiddos/dogs,
I've been thinking about next summer lately (yes I'm planning fairly far in advance) because unfortunately being home has produced a fairly Godless summer for me, and I saw some neato pics from the NMB kiddies, which got me thinking "hey a summer mission that isn't too expensive & allows for a job is a perfect way to not only be able to earn the money I need in order to go to college during the not summer, but also gives the opportunity of growing closer with God!" Long story short I went on the Cru website and discovered that there's more than NMB, or Paris, or Milwaukee and came across a summer mission in Yellowstone National Park. How wicked is that?! It's from May 29th-Aug 12th (11 weeks), you CAN get a job (yay!), and it costs $1850, which is a very reasonable amount to raise (plus a plane ticket which I also looked up to be about $300-400 roundtrip from MSP to BZN so more like $2300). I was wondering if there were any peeps out there in a similar predicament that would be interested in possibly going there next summer? I just think it would be a super neat & it would be nice to have a pal from the area to go with since we wouldn't be in Kansas anymore. This is all very theoretical at this point, I just wanted to get a feel for whether or nah there is anyone who loves a good national park and mountains and Jesus and wants to escape the suffocating environment of a fairly Godless home life for a summer. Hit me up if you're contemplating this, and even if the plans never actually solidify maybe we can be buds or something. Thank y'all for ya time.
Peace and Love turtle doves.

P.S. here is a pic of the beaut that is Yellowstone to coerce you into it

**Fall Job Posting/Opening**
HEY ALL!  If anyone is looking for a job this upcoming fall, I will be leaving the family I PCA for to start my MT internship (woohoo!)  Anyways the family has trusted me to find a replacement and so I thought to post on this page of wonderful people.  You would be taking care of a young boy who has autism & ADHD, but I say taking care very lightly, he is high functioning and you're basically just hanging out with a really cool kid who loves math, piano, and has perfect pitch (casual).  Hours are flexible, I worked 3 days a week during the school year, but there is room for more.  It pays well & is recommended if you have your own vehicle!  PLEASE PLEASE message me if you are at all interested, or would like more details!!  Keep enjoying the summer please~!

message: Hey everyone, I've got a friend whose sister is transferring to the U next year and is looking for some awesome Christian housing starting in August/fall. Anyone know of a spot? She is a junior and is super easygoing, social and looking to get connected. Let me know if you know of anyone who has a room!

Hey Guys, I hope you all are having a great Summer. There is a fantastic Christian Summer Camp called North Central Camp Cherith (http://www.camp-cherith.com/) that I attend every summer and now, I'm a counselor there. But this summer I am unable to make it. The director reached out to me today saying that the Lord has provided them with an abundance of campers within the past few days and now they are under staff. They are looking for some Godly men that want to make a difference in the lives of these children (1st-12th grade) who want to learn more about the Lord and sharing the Gospel with them. Camp starts this Saturday 6/18 and goes until Friday 6/24. This is a wonderful camp and this camp shaped me into the person who I am today. If you're interested or know anyone that is interested or just have questions please don't hesitate to contact me. My number is 763-381-1774, Thanks!

Hey Everyone!

Do you want to go to the TOGETHER 2016 event on July 16 at the National Mall, but you don't know how to get there? Good news! We have a way for you to get there! 

We are joining Cru and others from Fargo Metro area on their buses to worship God with many other brothers and sisters in Christ at the National Mall.

The deadline to sign up to ride with them is June 15th (that's one week!). The cost is about $230, including hotel and bus fares (not including food). We will be picked up in Minneapolis on Thursday and arrive back home in Minneapolis late on Sunday. We will be staying at the Hyatt Regency.

To sign up, follow this link: https://www.eventregistrationtool.com/#/register/e05fca77-dbe3-49a2-9625-bf04bf2a1cc6/page/

And for more details, check out the facebook event: https://www.facebook.com/events/1027429037345664/

Hello everybody!!! 
I hope you all are having an amazing summer so far!!! I have taken on the responsibility and am pleased to host the Minneapolis hub for summer connect with Cru this year! So if you are still interested in watching the live stream on Thursday nights at 7pm, it's free to sign up, or just come on over to the lighthouse! We don't have space for parking but there should be street parking. Message me if you have any questions or text me at 763-234-5586! Thanks everyone!

Hey all,
I know this maybe a long shot but I just went swing dancing again for the first time in two years and I forgot how much I miss it. I could never go when all of you went before because I always had rehearsals. However, school is over and I hope at least some of you will be in the cities next week. If you are/will be still here, would anyone be interested in going swing dancing next week at the caves?
God bless,
Reid

message: If anyone is looking for a part-time summer job, I have great news!  I am not going to be in town this summer and have to leave the family I PCA (Personal Care Assistant) for.  I got to work with an incredible 12-yr old boy with autism a couple nights a week and it was super fun.  You would need a car to drive him to various activities such as therapy, Tae Kwon Do, and trampolining at SkyZone.  If you are interested at all or have any questions, please message me!

Hey Crutons!

I know a lot of people went to Unite last night and that's so awesome!

Let's continue to pray for the people in our classes, dorms, apartment buildings, people back home, and our families! Join us one last time TOMORROW at 9:30am at COFFMAN (by the couches on first floor) to pray for our community.

I think it'd be awesome if we could pray for our communities as we head back home or to summer missions or people staying hear on campus. So come join us for one last week!

See ya there!

Thanks!

Hey everyone!

This Saturday will be the 2nd to last weekend we will be praying for our campus before summer. Summer brings people many different places with many opportunities and it can often be hard to find a way to continue to grow in your faith. 

Join us this Saturday at 8am at Coffman (before mug n muffin) so we can pray for the people here on campus and the summer they have ahead. 

Hope to see you this Saturday morning!

message:
Hey everyone! This has nothing to do with Jesus and everything to do with a statistics class I am taking but we are collecting data based on majors and handedness. I was trying to think of a place that I could post my group's survey and thought of this loving and wonderful bunch of people. It would really mean a lot if you could take 5 minutes out of your day to answer these 6 questions! Just ask yourselves, WWJD? :P

Disclaimer: Answering these questions is completely anonymous and optional. We are not collecting anyone's names or personal information. It is purely for a school project and will not be published. Once we turn in our project we are destroying all of our data too. :) 

Thank you so much everyone!! (Sorry for the spam) 

Here's the link:

Hey team! Be sure to think back about any times you've been able to have spiritual conversations/share the gospel in the past couple of weeks. The numbers that I got from texts this week and last week were pretty low, but I don't think that's because people weren't sharing the Gospel--just that people forgot to text it in--an easy thing to forget. So take a couple minutes and send those in : )

message:
Hey team. Scott and I sent an email out to our ministry partners a couple days before Dial-A-Donut and asked them to pray for you guys and so many people replied last week, sharing that they were praying for all of you. And then this evening, I emailed them a follow-up sharing some of what happened. There were a few responses in particular that I got last week and even already tonight that I wanted to share with you in hopes that you would be encouraged to know that people all over the midwest were praying for you and are now celebrating with you!

Last week:
Praise, You Father for raising up laborers for the harvest!  Give them ears to hear You as You tell them what to say to each person they encounter, for You Father know the hearts of each young person, and You know exactly what You want them to hear! I praise You Lord for putting Your heart into these young warriors, and may they experience You in a bold and mighty and also a tender and merciful way today.  Hallelujah Sweet Jesus!!

Tonight:
PRAISE GOD for the great job these young missionaries yes this outreach team are missionaries ! Their faces radiant the light of Jesus.

Oh, glory!!! What a tremendous idea! How many people would be willing to consider Christ if they simply had such an opportunity as this one afforded. I'm so excited for you all and the students whom the Lord is drawing. Thank you, thank you!

message:
SENIORS: Hey y'all! As some of you know, I'm currently involved in a TV reporting class and will be doing my final story of the year on Cru/Shift. I'm hoping to talk to a couple of you about your experience in Cru and what it's like being in a "religious affiliated" group on campus for a majority of your college experience. SOOO, if you're willing to be interviewed on camera this Wednesday before or after Shift, please let me know in the comments or in a personal message.

Also, there are about 20 students in my class who will watch this and, based on conversations, none of them are believers. This is a super cool opportunity to talk about Cru, the love of Christ, and why He is worthy of our praise and worship during college. Like I said, let me know in the comments or message me if you're interested.

Thanks guys!

P.S. This means I'll be filming parts of Shift on Wednesday. So, don't freak out if there's a camera in front of you!

message:
Hello everyone! 

I'm sure you're all sick of me and donut posts by now, but I have one more announcement!

First, I want to thank everyone again for all your work yesterday. It was so encouraging to see everyone's willingness and excitement to go out sharing.
Here's the kicker: we still have donuts left. Sooo, I'm going to be sharing in Coffman/the mall today with donuts from 11-2. If anyone is free during that time I would love to have you join me! message:
Hi there! It's me, Helen. Your friendly neighborhood spokesperson for Dial A Donut. I know you are all probably getting sick of seeing these posts about this but please read on and hear my heart. Jesus is telling me this is important.

Tomorrow from 10am to 3pm is Dial a Donut, as you are probably already aware; however, this post is not to ask you to volunteer to deliver donuts. Although if you would still like to it's not too late to sign up. This post is asking for help in a different way. I urge you, my brothers and sisters, as I have been convicted of not praying over this event, to please join me in asking the Lord to intercede and allow us to share His word. We are incapable of doing this on our own. I know some of you were looking for ways to help but have no time tomorrow, well, this is what you can do. Please pray for this outreach, because prayer is the most powerful weapon Jesus has given us. 

Pray for the students who are questioning who the Lord is. Pray that there would be curious hearts. Ask God in all boldness to provide 600 conversations in 5 hours (because that's how many donuts we have). He is so capable of accomplishing this. Go to Him in complete faith that He will provide the organization and efficiency to deliver this many donuts in a timely manner. And pray that the Devil would be out of this place. Pray that he would run far away from here because He has no power over us as His children. And pray that our hearts would be resilient to the battle that will take place tomorrow. This outreach is going to be huge, so the Devil will try all he can to attack it. I ask that you would join this battle in asking that the Lord would take over and we would step back.

Please take some time to pray over this outreach over the next 22 hours. I expect that Jesus will answer the cries of His people. I pray that we would be in pain for the lost on this campus and that would draw us to call out to the Lord in complete humility. I expect that He will show up and do His work.

Hey ya'll
It's Wednesday
Which means -- there will be sharing in Coffman today from 6:15-7:15 
We will meet at the top of the escalators!
Come join me and the squad for a low quality selfie (or high quality, however you wanna view it) and spreading the Gospel to our lovely campus.

It's a privilege to be used by God like this to win His children, and our brothers and sisters back.
If you haven't gone before, but want to check it out, we will set you up to share with someone who is comfortable sharing üôÉ 
Have a great day, and I'll see you there!

Do you ever think to yourself, "Gee, I wish there was a way to go sharing AND fulfill my lifelong dream of being a Krispy Kreme delivery person"?

If you answered yes then you're in luck because THIS Thursday from 10-3 you can do both of those things! We are still looking for volunteers to help deliver donuts to students who text in a question about Christianity. This is a great opportunity to engage students in spiritual conversations and, hopefully, share the gospel with them. message:
Hi everyone!  It's April 16th, which means that the annual University of Minnesota Unlimited Dance Marathon is here!  The event is a once a year big event in efforts to fundraise for kids who suffer from serious medical conditions at the Masonic Children's Hospital.  The event is FREE from 10am to 10pm in the Sports Pavilion,  and breakfast lunch and dinner is served for dancers. You can come and go as you wish,  but I'd really encourage you to stay as long as you are able to- we as college students are able to create such a big impact on the kids, who see us standing alongside them against their illness. I'd like to see you there if you are able to,  Dance Marathon is a great and not to mention fun way to make a difference.  Please message me in any way of you have questions!

Do you like free food? Do you like fun games? Do you like dancing? Well if you answered yes, no, or maybe to any of these then the Unlimited Dance Marathon is PERFECT for you! Come to the Sports Pavilion between 10am and 10pm on APRIL 16th to have the time of your life! Learn some new grooves AND help our Brave kids! All of the families we support have either one or more chronically ill children and are going to share their stories! Feel free to register online or at the door the day of. There is already a Cru team registered so join in and come along!

message:
Hey fellow Cru-tons!

This semester God has really laid on my heart the importance and power of prayer for those with lost hearts here on campus. I would like to encourage YOU to join me and other students to fulfill God's mission to pray for others and pray as a community.

Come join us in praying for the hearts of those on campus at Coffman every Saturday for the rest of the semester at 8:30am (I know it's early).

Remember that when we pray, God moves!

Hope to see you there!

message: Hey ya'll!! So tomorrow instead of the traditional Friday mornings at the Purple Onion we are going to take Project Abide on a field trip to stand alongside IJM and those around the world, and in our city, who are victims of modern day slavery. God has a heart for justice - please consider seeking His heart with us tomorrow morning on the front steps of Coffman! I will be there from 9:30-11 but Stand for Freedom is happening all day long. Thankful for your hearts to reflect Jesus in my life and I'm excited to see your lovely morning faces!!!

Hey all! If you don't have anything going on tonight, the IJM Stand4Freedom campaign is hosting a free concert at Sojourn Campus Church at 8pm featuring Remedy Drive! Donations are optional, but will help fund an IJM Rescue Operation.
It would be wonderful to see y'all there for an evening of alternative rock and justice!

message:
So my friend Jonathan Murphy from Chi Alpha has a message for you guys.

"For this coming year, I am looking to establish a Christian Student Union on campus that would function to 1) Bring unity to the on Christian community/ campus ministries and 2) Serve the Christian community and campus ministries. One Church will then become one of the methods or facets through which we bring unity. I am looking for 3-4 other mature Christian students who would be interested in being part of our leadership team. If you, or anyone you know has a heart and passion for our campus and Christian Unity, please PM or email me at murp0794@umn.edu, I would love to buy you a cup of coffee. 

If you have the ability and could share this message through any other ministry pages you are connected to (like Cru, Navs, A2F) it would be GREATLY appreciated!"

So if you guys are interested, let him know.

message:
Hey team! :D Do you deal with depression, anxiety, or any other type of mental wellness issue? Well I sure do, and many other Crutons do too! Come to my house Saturday at 11:30am and I'll make you waffles! :D

In addition to waffles, these weekly get-togethers I host for those of us dealing with mental wellness struggles exists for the express purpose of talking about our feelings and experiences, and getting support from others who are going through the same types of things. I was very skeptical about this type of thing before I started being a part of it, but it's seriously SO life-giving! Don't struggle with this kind of stuff alone!

If you would be at all interested in being a part of this type of thing either this weekend or in the future, message me like 'hey I'm interested maybe'. If you think somebody you know might be interested, message me their name :) They don't have to be a Cruton, or even completely sold on this whole Jesus-thing (just most of us are, and that's a big part of us overcoming stuff.)

Pros: I have a kitten who loves meeting new people. Also, waffles.
Cons: Getting out of bed/leaving my house is hard and people/new experiences are scary. (All very valid. If you think any of those things might hinder you, message me anyway!)

message:
Suh dudes---

So as some of you know, campus elections (Student Body President and Vice President) are coming up on April 6th-8th at vote.umn.edu. I know this is a weird way of putting it, but we can really be stewards of our vote. Only about 20% of students end up voting, so your vote could really REALLY make a difference. 

There's a debate between the two people running for President on this Thursday (the 31st) from 6-8pm in MCB 3-120. They'll be debating on topics such as diversity, mental health, social justice, etc. (aka things we should all care about as Christians/as regular people lol). 

So long story short- come to the debate on Thursday to get informed on how we can best love and serve this campus through its leaders. If you want to meet somewhere beforehand to have a lil cru crew to walk in with, hit me up. If you want a ride to MCB bc you live far away, also hit me up, as I would be happy to drive you.

If you don't want to come for the debate, come to get updated on what our campus will be looking like in the next year.
If you don't want to come for the campus update, come to listen and pray for our school.
If you don't want to come to listen and pray, come for the free Qdoba.

That's right, free Qdoba starting at 5:30. See y'all there.

Please reach out to one of us if you or anyone you know is interested or just have questions. Thanks!

Hey ya'll
So I am venturing off to be a camp counselor for the entirety of my  summer (yay!!!)
So that means I am in need of a sub-leaser for my spot in the Lighthouse. I currently share a room with my wonderful roommate Rachel Kelly (she rocks) who also is in need of someone to take her spot (potentially)
We pay $413 a month (SO CHEAP) but in the summer it will be $393 to live there.
If you, or you and a friend need a place to stay for cheap or if you know someone, please contact me through Facebook messenger, or commenting! Thanks!
